EVAR practice and outcomes since 1996

Martin Hennessy

11/06/2019

1 Details about all EVARs performed

  • This document covers EVARs performed between 1996-09-19 and 2019-06-05

1.1 Indication for and number of EVARs

Indications for EVARs performed since 1996. Both ruptured and symptomatic aneurysms are judged by available clinical information. Open repair issue is usually pseudoaneurym formation.

1.2 Site of EVAR

National Health Service (NHS) health board in which EVAR was performed. FV = Forth Valley, GG & C = Greater Glasgow and Clyde.

2.2 Age

  • Boxplots are used frequently in this section
  • The ‘box’ represents the interquartile range (IQR) of the data
  • In other words, 50% of the patients fall between this age range
  • The thick black horizontal line is the median age
  • The thin black vertical lines extend to the upper and lower limits of age
  • Black dots represent outliers (above or below 3 x IQR)
